47. Fauno: a deified prinee of ancient Latium, regarded as a god of shep- herds, as well as a god of prophecy. He was identified by the Greeks and later Romans with the Greek Pan. Marica: the guardian deity of the river Liris, She is here called Laurentian, or Latian, because Latium was bounded at one period by the Liris.
